-- Liverpool Says Managing Director Christian Purslow to Step Down From Post
-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 2010-10-20T13:21:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/liverpool-says-managing-director-christian-purslow-to-step-down-from-post.html
Liverpool soccer club said managing
director Christian Purslow is stepping down after the sale of
the team to New England Sports Ventures LLC.  Purslow will remain as a non-executive director and will
act as an advisor to the new owners, the team said today in an
e-mailed statement. The team is looking for a chief executive
officer.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  